- Obviously.

1289
00:56:36.270 --> 00:56:37.480
It's not like he's got two other wives

1290
00:56:37.560 --> 00:56:39.360
that he'd have lunch with one
and dinner with the other.

1291
00:56:39.430 --> 00:56:40.050
Right?

1292
00:56:40.270 --> 00:56:41.230
Obviously.

1293
00:56:41.310 --> 00:56:42.060
Pass me the knife.

1294
00:56:42.310 --> 00:56:43.150
Why?

1295
00:56:43.350 --> 00:56:44.390
Need to cut his tongue.

1296
00:56:44.730 --> 00:56:45.690
He's a jinx.

1297
00:56:45.850 --> 00:56:48.510
Why would anyone who has such
a lovely wife have two other wives?

1298
00:56:48.640 --> 00:56:49.760
That's exactly what I said.

1299
00:56:49.890 --> 00:56:51.510
You should talk less. You...

1300
00:56:52.480 --> 00:56:53.650
By the way. where's your brother?

1301
00:56:53.770 --> 00:56:54.610
Haven't seen him around.

1302
00:56:54.730 --> 00:56:56.020
He's gone out for some work.

1303
00:56:56.100 --> 00:56:56.970
He went back to Goa?

1304
00:56:57.060 --> 00:56:58.440
Not that far.

1305
00:56:58.850 --> 00:57:00.100
You know tomorrow's my birthday?

1306
00:57:00.180 --> 00:57:01.300
He went to book a cake for me.

1307
00:57:01.390 --> 00:57:02.470
It's your birthday?

1308
00:57:02.560 --> 00:57:03.400
Why didn't you tell me?

1309
00:57:03.810 --> 00:57:04.900
Why did he have to step out for that?

1310
00:57:04.980 --> 00:57:06.150
We could've just ordered it online.

1311
00:57:06.310 --> 00:57:08.610
No. when he goes in the police jeep.

1312
00:57:08.770 --> 00:57:09.810
he gets a better discount.

1313
00:57:09.890 --> 00:57:11.550
I even told him
to grab some groceries.

1314
00:57:12.180 --> 00:57:14.890
Sister. got your groceries
and everything.

1315
00:57:15.310 --> 00:57:19.650
and I invited a few of our
relatives for your birthday.

1316
00:57:19.770 --> 00:57:21.110
Then let's invite
Michael's parents as well.

1317
00:57:21.180 --> 00:57:22.010
My parents?

1318
00:57:22.230 --> 00:57:24.020
No. no... they don't meet anyone.

1319
00:57:24.180 --> 00:57:25.220
Not even each other.

1320
00:57:25.310 --> 00:57:26.110
Very strange.

1321
00:57:26.230 --> 00:57:27.020
Why not?

1322
00:57:27.100 --> 00:57:28.010
Why not?

1323
00:57:28.730 --> 00:57:29.940
He searched for them everywhere.

1324
00:57:30.020 --> 00:57:30.900
but couldn't find either of them.

1325
00:57:31.100 --> 00:57:32.220
They got lost at the Kumbh Mela.

1326
00:57:33.430 --> 00:57:34.970
Christian parents got lost
at the Kumbh Mela?!

1327
00:57:35.480 --> 00:57:36.480
They were both police officers.

1328
00:57:36.600 --> 00:57:38.140
Since people always
go missing there.

1329
00:57:38.230 --> 00:57:39.310
they were on duty to help others.

1330
00:57:39.350 --> 00:57:39.930
Yeah.

1331
00:57:40.020 --> 00:57:41.230
So while trying to stop
others from getting lost.

1332
00:57:41.270 --> 00:57:42.230
they ended up lost themselves.

1333
00:57:42.350 --> 00:57:43.430
Wait a minute.

1334
00:57:44.680 --> 00:57:45.930
How do police
officers even get lost?

1335
00:57:46.100 --> 00:57:47.220
How would I know?

1336
00:57:47.310 --> 00:57:48.520
Go ask in UP.

1337
00:57:48.680 --> 00:57:49.720
Why should he go there. Mohan?

1338
00:57:49.810 --> 00:57:50.520
Mohan?

1339
00:57:50.640 --> 00:57:53.680
Ganj. Mohan Ganj.
their last known location.

1340
00:57:53.890 --> 00:57:56.550
Aren't you here because
Father Anthony asked you to find

1341
00:57:56.640 --> 00:57:57.850
- that guy who married three times?
- Yes.

1342
00:57:57.930 --> 00:57:58.430
Right?

1343
00:57:58.560 --> 00:57:59.690
- You're right.
- Yes.

1344
00:57:59.810 --> 00:58:00.860
Focus. focus.

1345
00:58:01.230 --> 00:58:01.690
Right?

1346
00:58:01.850 --> 00:58:04.470
I'll catch the guy
who married three times.

1347
00:58:04.600 --> 00:58:06.850
then I'll catch your parents.

1348
00:58:06.930 --> 00:58:07.970
I mean... I'm sorry.
I'll find your parents.

1349
00:58:08.140 --> 00:58:09.010
It's a promise.

1350
00:58:11.730 --> 00:58:12.730
Okay. thank you.

1351
00:58:13.020 --> 00:58:13.860
That's enough.

1352
00:58:15.520 --> 00:58:16.480
Hubby. listen.

1353
00:58:17.180 --> 00:58:18.600
don't call me when I'm here.

1354
00:58:19.100 --> 00:58:20.800
The women here pick up anyone's calls.

1355
00:58:20.890 --> 00:58:21.890
Hang up now.

1356
00:58:23.140 --> 00:58:24.260
Meera?

1357
00:58:27.730 --> 00:58:29.480
I've got dessert for you.

1358
00:58:31.430 --> 00:58:34.850
Listen. this Friday.
we'll keep a Roza (fast) together.

1359
00:58:35.270 --> 00:58:36.150
Roza?

1360
00:58:36.310 --> 00:58:37.230
Hmm.

1361
00:58:37.480 --> 00:58:39.730
I'd made a vow that
after our wedding.

1362
00:58:39.810 --> 00:58:41.940
we'd fast together for a day.

1363
00:58:42.310 --> 00:58:44.150
So this Friday. we'll fast together.

1364
00:58:44.560 --> 00:58:45.900
Come home early.

1365
00:58:45.980 --> 00:58:47.440
We'll break our fast together
in the evening.

1366
00:58:48.480 --> 00:58:49.650
Eat. Wait. I'll feed you.

1367
00:58:49.730 --> 00:58:50.560
No!

1368
00:58:50.730 --> 00:58:52.150
We'll break our fast together. right?

1369
00:58:53.600 --> 00:58:55.260
Whose phone is vibrating?

1370
00:58:58.640 --> 00:59:00.140
What's wrong?

1371
00:59:01.100 --> 00:59:01.930
Are you okay?

1372
00:59:02.480 --> 00:59:03.980
That noise is coming
from my chest.

1373
00:59:04.180 --> 00:59:05.300
I swallowed a black cardamom whole.

1374
00:59:06.270 --> 00:59:07.400
Want me to get you some water?

1375
00:59:07.520 --> 00:59:08.440
Hmm.

1376
00:59:08.770 --> 00:59:10.190
Let me take your plate.

1377
00:59:11.140 --> 00:59:12.640
Looks like you really
liked the biryani.

1378
00:59:12.730 --> 00:59:14.400
I'll go get you some water.

1379
00:59:29.180 --> 00:59:30.180
Does this look good. Mr. Mirza?

1380
00:59:30.270 --> 00:59:31.730
Yes. it does.
but I want you to try this one.

1381
00:59:31.980 --> 00:59:33.810
You'll make me try
the whole shop?

1382
00:59:33.890 --> 00:59:35.180
Come on. try it on.
you'll look amazing.

1383
00:59:35.270 --> 00:59:36.310
I can't keep going inside.

1384
00:59:36.390 --> 00:59:37.260
I'll change here itself.

1385
00:59:40.680 --> 00:59:41.720
Hey... don't look.

1386
00:59:49.270 --> 00:59:50.480
I've tried on 150 kurtas already.

1387
00:59:51.680 --> 00:59:52.350
Wonderful.

1388
00:59:52.430 --> 00:59:54.100
You look great.

1389
00:59:54.230 --> 00:59:55.610
Now try this cap too.

1390
00:59:55.730 --> 00:59:57.520
- It's great.
- Hmm.

1391
01:00:00.850 --> 01:00:02.550
I'll try it inside.

1392
01:00:04.730 --> 01:00:05.270
Huh?

1393
01:00:05.350 --> 01:00:07.390
Strange. he wore the pajamas
in open view.

1394
01:00:07.480 --> 01:00:08.690
but for a cap he needs a room?

1395
01:00:09.480 --> 01:00:11.400
Listen. I'll wait for you outside.

1396
01:00:13.390 --> 01:00:14.220
Excuse me...

1397
01:00:14.310 --> 01:00:15.060
Yes?

1398
01:00:15.390 --> 01:00:16.390
Where's Mehmood?

1399
01:00:18.020 --> 01:00:19.020
Over there.

1400
01:00:23.810 --> 01:00:24.610
Mehmood!

1401
01:00:27.890 --> 01:00:28.850
Mehmood!

1402
01:00:29.930 --> 01:00:30.850
Come on out.

1403
01:00:31.140 --> 01:00:32.470
I know you are in there.

1404
01:00:34.270 --> 01:00:36.400
Mehmood. are you going
to step out or not?

1405
01:00:38.480 --> 01:00:39.480
Yes. sir. how can I help you?

1406
01:00:40.060 --> 01:00:41.020
I'm Mehmood.

1407
01:00:42.060 --> 01:00:43.770
You got married three times?

1408
01:00:44.060 --> 01:00:44.940
Three times?

1409
01:00:45.020 --> 01:00:46.360
Who told you that. sir?

1410
01:00:46.480 --> 01:00:47.940
Someone's filed a complaint
against you.

1411
01:00:48.140 --> 01:00:49.600
A complaint? Against me?

1412
01:00:49.890 --> 01:00:51.680
Was it Jameel. sir?

1413
01:00:51.770 --> 01:00:52.980
Yeah. Jameel.

1414
01:00:53.230 --> 01:00:54.360
Sir. he's a liar.

1415
01:00:54.430 --> 01:00:56.220
Sir. he's lying! Ever since
I kicked him out.

1416
01:00:56.270 --> 01:00:58.360
he's been spreading nonsense
about me.

1417
01:00:58.680 --> 01:00:59.760
Arrest him. sir--

1418
01:00:59.850 --> 01:01:01.140
Why should I arrest him?

1419
01:01:01.230 --> 01:01:03.020
I cannot lose my focus.

1420
01:01:03.230 --> 01:01:04.400
I'll catch the one
who changed his religion

1421
01:01:04.480 --> 01:01:06.400
and got married thrice first.

1422
01:01:06.520 --> 01:01:07.770
Do you understand?

1423
01:01:09.350 --> 01:01:10.510
That was a woman?

1424
01:01:10.890 --> 01:01:12.010
She's got a very manly hand.

1425
01:01:12.180 --> 01:01:13.100
Let's go.

1426
01:01:14.640 --> 01:01:16.260
Ma'am. I'm here
with my son-in-law.

1427
01:01:16.350 --> 01:01:18.050
Meet me in the evening.
I'll give you my number.

1428
01:01:18.230 --> 01:01:19.310
Don't get too excited. it's me.

1429
01:01:19.430 --> 01:01:20.430
Why are you wearing a burqa?!

1430
01:01:20.520 --> 01:01:21.060
What are you doing?

1431
01:01:21.180 --> 01:01:22.220
Should I try on clothes
only for myself?

1432
01:01:22.310 --> 01:01:23.360
Should I not buy anything for Ruhi?

1433
01:01:23.520 --> 01:01:24.520
Let's go.

1434
01:01:25.020 --> 01:01:27.110
Listen. the pooja items
they sent are all wrong.

1435
01:01:27.230 --> 01:01:28.900
I've sent you a new list.
Bring it along.

1436
01:01:29.020 --> 01:01:29.980
Fine.

1437
01:01:30.390 --> 01:01:32.350
Mr. Mirza. we need
to go to the market.

1438
01:01:32.560 --> 01:01:33.060
Fine.

1439
01:01:33.230 --> 01:01:34.810
You shouldn't have
troubled Mohan for it.

1440
01:01:34.890 --> 01:01:37.100
I told his father to get those things.

1441
01:01:37.270 --> 01:01:38.860
It's fine Ã¢Â€Â” Navratri's going on.

1442
01:01:38.980 --> 01:01:40.690
we'll need all this every
day anyway. right?

1443
01:01:40.770 --> 01:01:41.270
Hmm.

1444
01:01:41.310 --> 01:01:42.440
Please stop right here.

1445
01:01:44.980 --> 01:01:46.190
Wait here. I'll go and get the stuff.

1446
01:01:46.270 --> 01:01:47.400
- Hurry up.
- Hold this.

1447
01:01:53.230 --> 01:01:54.400
And here's the coconut.

1448
01:01:54.480 --> 01:01:55.310
Coconut.

1449
01:01:56.350 --> 01:01:57.970
Sir. pack everything on this list.

1450
01:02:00.100 --> 01:02:01.930
You do pooja at your place too. sir?

1451
01:02:02.100 --> 01:02:02.970
Yeah. why?

1452
01:02:03.270 --> 01:02:04.650
No problem. I'll get all this.

1453
01:02:06.230 --> 01:02:08.270
Give me a red veil for the Goddess.

1454
01:02:09.430 --> 01:02:11.100
Sir. is this one okay?

1455
01:02:12.390 --> 01:02:14.350
Yes. it's red. Give me that one.

1456
01:02:18.930 --> 01:02:21.220
Sir. you forgot your phone.

1457
01:02:29.640 --> 01:02:31.260
Come on. come on.
let's go. Mr. Mirza.

1458
01:02:31.310 --> 01:02:32.610
Hey. what's the rush?
Come on. let's go already.

1459
01:02:32.680 --> 01:02:35.970
They sell stuff for funerals too.
Want me to grab some for you?

1460
01:02:36.600 --> 01:02:38.930
They buy pooja items too?

1461
01:02:39.020 --> 01:02:40.360
Sir. this is what we've always wanted.

1462
01:02:40.430 --> 01:02:42.760
we celebrate their Eid.
and they celebrate our Diwali.

1463
01:02:42.890 --> 01:02:45.640
But when it's about marriage.
we should stick to our own faith.

1464
01:02:45.730 --> 01:02:46.690
- Our own faith.
- Yes.

1465
01:02:46.890 --> 01:02:47.970
Got it. sir.

1466
01:02:48.100 --> 01:02:48.970
You're absolutely right.

1467
01:02:55.180 --> 01:02:58.720
Son. Surleen liked you
the moment she saw your photo.

1468
01:02:59.680 --> 01:03:00.510
Mom!

1469
01:03:01.180 --> 01:03:02.260
Son. you tell us.

1470
01:03:02.930 --> 01:03:04.050
what do you think about our Surleen?

1471
01:03:04.140 --> 01:03:05.390
He's over the moon.

1472
01:03:05.480 --> 01:03:06.650
A tea drinker's been handed a smoothie Ã¢Â€Â”

1473
01:03:06.730 --> 01:03:07.770
what more could he want?

1474
01:03:12.060 --> 01:03:13.810
We're talking about
your marriage. son.

1475
01:03:14.230 --> 01:03:16.060
Don't you think you should've
brought an elder along?

1476
01:03:16.230 --> 01:03:18.650
Uncle. he's an expert
when it comes to weddings.

1477
01:03:18.890 --> 01:03:19.640
You name it...

1478
01:03:19.730 --> 01:03:21.900
Hindu marriage. Muslim marriage.
Christian wedding...

1479
01:03:21.980 --> 01:03:22.730
he's done them all.

1480
01:03:22.890 --> 01:03:23.970
He hasn't missed a single one.

1481
01:03:24.180 --> 01:03:25.970
Done...
he means I have attended them all.

1482
01:03:26.100 --> 01:03:29.890
Just like I'll attend his
Punjabi wedding.

1483
01:03:30.350 --> 01:03:31.760
Attend... he attended them.

1484
01:03:31.890 --> 01:03:33.470
Hello! Hi!

1485
01:03:33.560 --> 01:03:35.020
Sorry. Aunty. I'm late.

1486
01:03:35.100 --> 01:03:36.260
Don't be late for her wedding.

1487
01:03:36.350 --> 01:03:38.640
No! Oh. Surleen.
you look so beautiful.

1488
01:03:39.060 --> 01:03:41.360
Dear. meet him...
our future son-in-law.

1489
01:03:42.270 --> 01:03:43.270
Hello.

1490
01:03:44.310 --> 01:03:45.310
This guy?

1491
01:03:46.140 --> 01:03:48.100
You're marrying Surleen to him?

1492
01:03:48.560 --> 01:03:49.440
Yes. why?

1493
01:03:49.560 --> 01:03:51.360
He already has three wives!

1494
01:03:51.520 --> 01:03:52.690
- What?
- What?

1495
01:03:52.770 --> 01:03:53.900
- What?
- What?

1496
01:03:54.140 --> 01:03:55.180
You have three wives?

1497
01:03:55.270 --> 01:03:56.940
No Uncle. I don't even have one.

1498
01:03:57.100 --> 01:03:58.050
He has three.

1499
01:03:58.140 --> 01:03:59.430
Forget him. no one
can have three wives.

1500
01:03:59.520 --> 01:04:00.690
- No one has a death wish.
- Right.

1501
01:04:00.810 --> 01:04:02.270
You've misunderstood. ma'am.

1502
01:04:02.310 --> 01:04:03.520
No misunderstanding.

1503
01:04:03.600 --> 01:04:07.390
I've seen three women
calling him Hubby.

1504
01:04:07.520 --> 01:04:09.650
That's my name...
Harvinder Singh aka Hubby.

1505
01:04:09.730 --> 01:04:10.610
Everyone calls me Hubby.

1506
01:04:10.680 --> 01:04:12.430
Yeah. even I call him Hubby.

1507
01:04:12.520 --> 01:04:14.060
Does that make me his wife then?

1508
01:04:14.770 --> 01:04:16.360
If you still don't trust him.

1509
01:04:16.520 --> 01:04:17.610
then forget the whole thing.

1510
01:04:17.730 --> 01:04:19.270
- Let's go. Hubby.
- What are you saying. bro?

1511
01:04:19.350 --> 01:04:20.390
We didn't come here to get insulted.

1512
01:04:20.480 --> 01:04:21.480
I don't mind it.

1513
01:04:21.560 --> 01:04:22.900
Sit down. don't take
it the wrong way.

1514
01:04:22.980 --> 01:04:24.560
No. no. we're not offended.

1515
01:04:24.730 --> 01:04:26.520
She runs an NGO...

1516
01:04:26.640 --> 01:04:29.220
"Chase Away the Romeos
and Save the Daughter!"

1517
01:04:29.350 --> 01:04:32.100
She suspects everyone.

1518
01:04:32.180 --> 01:04:33.390
That is not right.

1519
01:04:34.020 --> 01:04:35.860
Mr. Hubby. do you mind
if I take a picture of you?

1520
01:04:40.890 --> 01:04:41.890
Smile. please.

1521
01:04:42.520 --> 01:04:43.310
Very good.

1522
01:04:43.480 --> 01:04:46.480
I'll teach you a lesson later...
I'll expose you.

1523
01:04:48.890 --> 01:04:50.390
Why did D.D. call us here?

1524
01:05:01.180 --> 01:05:03.140
Come on. there's someone
I want you to meet.

1525
01:05:03.890 --> 01:05:05.220
Who does he want us to meet?

1526
01:05:12.640 --> 01:05:13.600
Meet him...

1527
01:05:14.430 --> 01:05:15.640
he's come all the way from Goa.

1528
01:05:16.230 --> 01:05:17.230
Father Anthony.

1529
01:05:21.020 --> 01:05:23.940
Father Anthony hasn't seen
the face of the man

1530
01:05:24.270 --> 01:05:26.310
who kept changing his religion
and got married three times.

1531
01:05:26.730 --> 01:05:29.940
but he says he can recognize
him just by his voice.

1532
01:05:33.350 --> 01:05:35.510
Here. there's a confession written
on this paper. Read it.

1533
01:05:41.640 --> 01:05:42.970
Read the confession.

1534
01:05:47.560 --> 01:05:48.690
Read it.

1535
01:05:52.140 --> 01:05:53.180
Begin.

1536
01:05:58.270 --> 01:06:00.230
Father Anthony is listening...
speak up.

1537
01:06:00.270 --> 01:06:03.690
<i>The first...</i>

1538
01:06:03.810 --> 01:06:07.110
<i>The second...</i>

1539
01:06:07.230 --> 01:06:08.860
<i>The third...</i>

1540
01:06:08.930 --> 01:06:10.100
<i>All alone!</i>

1541
01:06:28.730 --> 01:06:29.980
Read the confession.

1542
01:06:34.980 --> 01:06:36.650
Father Anthony is listening... speak up.

1543
01:06:39.310 --> 01:06:40.520
Read it.

1544
01:06:49.480 --> 01:06:52.230
It's natural to get scared
when your friend's about to get caught.

1545
01:06:54.230 --> 01:06:59.060
Look at poor Michael.
sweating bullets just because you got caught.

1546
01:07:00.480 --> 01:07:01.690
- I got caught?
- Yeah.

1547
01:07:02.600 --> 01:07:05.760
You thought you can hide behind Michael?

1548
01:07:06.520 --> 01:07:07.480
- I...
- Read the confession.

1549
01:07:08.680 --> 01:07:09.720
Sir. I didn't...

1550
01:07:09.810 --> 01:07:11.860
Sit down and read the confession.

1551
01:07:21.430 --> 01:07:23.180
Father. there's this girl I love.

1552
01:07:23.270 --> 01:07:24.980
For her. I turned from Hindu to Muslim.

1553
01:07:25.100 --> 01:07:26.550
then to Christian.

1554
01:07:26.730 --> 01:07:28.560
And now you have become a Sikh.

1555
01:07:28.980 --> 01:07:30.650
No. Father. I have always been a Sikh.

1556
01:07:31.600 --> 01:07:33.430
Really? Then read it.

1557
01:07:37.020 --> 01:07:40.650
Father. I've made a huge mistake.

1558
01:07:40.730 --> 01:07:46.480
I've married three women
of three different faiths.

1559
01:07:46.850 --> 01:07:50.640
but I still want a fourth.

1560
01:07:50.680 --> 01:07:51.720
I remember!

1561
01:07:52.850 --> 01:07:54.470
I remember it so clearly!

1562
01:07:54.640 --> 01:07:57.140
He's not that Bhopali.

1563
01:07:57.680 --> 01:08:00.100
- What?
- He's not that Bhopali.

1564
01:08:00.270 --> 01:08:01.560
He's not our guy.

1565
01:08:01.640 --> 01:08:04.390
See sir. I told you it's not me.

1566
01:08:05.230 --> 01:08:07.110
But what made you suspect me?

1567
01:08:07.270 --> 01:08:09.440
Actually.
a girl filed a complaint against him...

1568
01:08:09.520 --> 01:08:11.060
Santosh. who works for some NGO.

1569
01:08:11.140 --> 01:08:13.050
Sir. I am suspicious about a boy.

1570
01:08:13.310 --> 01:08:17.480
He's already married thrice
and he is about to ruin another girl's life.

1571
01:08:17.560 --> 01:08:20.650
Call him to the police station. hang him
upside down and question him. sir.

1572
01:08:20.680 --> 01:08:22.350
- Who is this boy?
- Show him the photo.

1573
01:08:24.640 --> 01:08:26.800
She filed a complaint
that you are married thrice...

1574
01:08:27.100 --> 01:08:28.260
and are about to get married
for the fourth time.

1575
01:08:28.680 --> 01:08:30.890
But sorry. Hubby.
you aren't the one I'm looking for.

1576
01:08:31.020 --> 01:08:32.650
I'm sorry. Father. for wasting your time.

1577
01:08:32.680 --> 01:08:34.720
No problem. David. No problem at all.

1578
01:08:34.850 --> 01:08:37.220
I just hope that man gets caught soon.

1579
01:08:40.520 --> 01:08:41.520
By the way. who's this?

1580
01:08:42.310 --> 01:08:44.770
Oh. I'm so sorry.
I forgot to introduce you to him.

1581
01:08:44.850 --> 01:08:47.600
Father. he is my brother-in-law Michael.

1582
01:08:47.640 --> 01:08:48.680
Michael!

1583
01:08:48.770 --> 01:08:49.770
I see! I see!

1584
01:08:49.850 --> 01:08:53.930
I heard from David how you saved Jenny.
married her.

1585
01:08:54.020 --> 01:08:55.480
Very good boy.

1586
01:08:55.600 --> 01:08:56.640
God bless you.

1587
01:08:58.520 --> 01:08:59.520
He can't talk?

1588
01:08:59.640 --> 01:09:01.550
He does. Say something.

1589
01:09:02.640 --> 01:09:03.760
He can't.

1590
01:09:03.930 --> 01:09:05.300
He's observing a Maun Vrat today.

1591
01:09:05.390 --> 01:09:06.470
Silent fasting.

1592
01:09:06.730 --> 01:09:10.860
Son. I know Maun Vrat is silent fasting!

1593
01:09:10.930 --> 01:09:13.050
I know Hindi. Sanskrit too.

1594
01:09:13.350 --> 01:09:18.890
Anyway. Michael. a husband
who stays quiet lives longer.

1595
01:09:19.810 --> 01:09:20.980
Like the wise ones say.

1596
01:09:21.060 --> 01:09:23.270
One moment of silence can bring
you a hundred moments of peace.

1597
01:09:23.350 --> 01:09:25.100
- See!
- I know Punjabi too.

1598
01:09:25.140 --> 01:09:26.510
Father knows a lot of language.

1599
01:09:26.600 --> 01:09:28.100
Come Father. I'll drop you.
Please come with me.

1600
01:09:28.180 --> 01:09:30.010
I know. I know Sindhi also.

1601
01:09:32.390 --> 01:09:34.970
Let me drop you. Please come with me.

1602
01:09:39.480 --> 01:09:41.110
Goddess saved me today.

1603
01:09:41.480 --> 01:09:42.610
Big time.

1604
01:09:42.810 --> 01:09:46.980
<i>Glory to you. O Mother Gauri.</i>

1605
01:09:47.060 --> 01:09:52.610
<i>Glory to you. O Holy Mother.</i>

1606
01:09:52.640 --> 01:09:56.600
<i>They meditate upon
you every day and night.</i>

1607
01:09:56.680 --> 01:10:00.600
<i>They meditate upon
Mother every day and night.</i>

1608
01:10:00.680 --> 01:10:04.800
<i>The powerful trinity -
Brahma. Vishnu and Shiva.</i>

1609
01:10:04.890 --> 01:10:09.600
<i>Glory to you. O Mother Gauri.</i>

1610
01:10:09.640 --> 01:10:10.640
Say...

1611
01:10:16.350 --> 01:10:19.800
<i>Glory to you. O Mother Gauri.</i>

1612
01:10:19.890 --> 01:10:23.390
<i>Glory to you. O Holy Mother.</i>

1613
01:10:26.390 --> 01:10:28.300
<i>God bless you with good fortune.</i>

1614
01:10:28.430 --> 01:10:30.260
<i>May God bless you with a live long.</i>

1615
01:10:30.350 --> 01:10:32.720
<i>May God bless you with prosperity.</i>

1616
01:10:33.180 --> 01:10:36.140
This offering if for the couple.

1617
01:10:36.230 --> 01:10:37.650
- Please make sure you consume it.
- Okay.

1618
01:10:40.140 --> 01:10:41.260
Come home early.

1619
01:10:41.430 --> 01:10:42.890
We'll break our fast together
in the evening.

1620
01:10:44.350 --> 01:10:46.550
I'll eat it later.
I've kept a Roza (fast).

1621
01:10:47.020 --> 01:10:47.940
Roza?

1622
01:10:48.890 --> 01:10:51.510
I'm keeping a fast for my wife.

1623
01:10:51.640 --> 01:10:53.100
You're fasting for me?

1624
01:10:53.270 --> 01:10:53.940
Yes.

1625
01:10:54.020 --> 01:10:57.190
If he's fasting for his wife
then he's obviously fasting for you.

1626
01:10:57.310 --> 01:11:00.310
It's not like he's some king
with three wives.

1627
01:11:00.390 --> 01:11:01.300
Well said. Uncle.

1628
01:11:01.390 --> 01:11:02.800
I was just about to say that.

1629
01:11:02.890 --> 01:11:04.010
What were you going to say?

1630
01:11:04.980 --> 01:11:05.980
Jai Mata Di (Glory to Mother Goddess).

1631
01:11:06.060 --> 01:11:07.900
- Jai Mata Di!
- Jai Mata Di!

1632
01:11:07.980 --> 01:11:12.060
Mohan. don't forget to eat the offerings
or the whole thing would go wrong.

1633
01:11:12.270 --> 01:11:14.020
Things are already going wrong.
I need to fix them.

1634
01:11:14.270 --> 01:11:15.060
Huh?

1635
01:11:15.560 --> 01:11:16.560
You have a banana?

1636
01:11:17.140 --> 01:11:18.600
- Jai Mata Di!
- Give me one more.

1637
01:11:18.640 --> 01:11:20.010
- Jai Mata Di!
- Jai Mata Di!

1638
01:11:21.850 --> 01:11:23.720
Get in the car. I'll go change.

1639
01:11:23.810 --> 01:11:24.810
Okay.

1640
01:11:25.060 --> 01:11:26.110
Bye. Aunty.

1641
01:11:30.020 --> 01:11:31.650
Let's go. let's go. let's go.
I'm running late.

1642
01:11:32.980 --> 01:11:33.940
Yeah Jenny. I'm coming.

1643
01:11:34.020 --> 01:11:35.690
Jenny? Who's Jenny?

1644
01:11:36.060 --> 01:11:37.060
It's Ruhi.

1645
01:11:38.020 --> 01:11:41.150
Right. that's what I said. Ruhi...
who's Jenny?

1646
01:11:41.230 --> 01:11:43.190
You said. "Jenny. I'm coming."

1647
01:11:43.270 --> 01:11:45.310
No. I said I'm just coming.

1648
01:11:45.390 --> 01:11:47.800
You're Ruhi and you're observing a fast.

1649
01:11:47.930 --> 01:11:48.720
It's not your birthday. is it?

1650
01:11:48.810 --> 01:11:50.020
What are you saying?

1651
01:11:50.100 --> 01:11:51.970
Anyway. that's why I called.

1652
01:11:52.060 --> 01:11:53.480
We have to break the fast at 6:15 pm.

1653
01:11:53.560 --> 01:11:55.110
If you are running late.
you can break the fast wherever you are.

1654
01:11:55.350 --> 01:11:56.260
we'll have dinner together.

1655
01:11:56.350 --> 01:11:57.600
So sweet of you. darling.

1656
01:11:57.640 --> 01:11:59.390
You're the only one who understands me.

1657
01:11:59.480 --> 01:12:00.360
Bye. see you in the evening.

1658
01:12:00.430 --> 01:12:01.720
Okay. bye.

1659
01:12:01.810 --> 01:12:02.650
What happened?

1660
01:12:02.680 --> 01:12:03.800
I can break my fast at 6:15 pm.

1661
01:12:03.890 --> 01:12:04.930
Let's go. let's go. let's go already.

1662
01:12:05.020 --> 01:12:06.270
I'm holding the Goddess's offerings.

1663
01:12:06.350 --> 01:12:07.430
and you've got to break your Roza
at 6:15pm.

1664
01:12:07.520 --> 01:12:08.770
I have no idea how you're going
to juggle all this.

1665
01:12:08.850 --> 01:12:11.510
So sorry. guys. so sorry.
I'm-I'm-I'm late. I'm late.

1666
01:12:11.600 --> 01:12:13.050
- Happy birthday. darling.
- Michael!

1667
01:12:13.140 --> 01:12:14.180
- Happy birthday.
- Please come. please come. everyone.

1668
01:12:14.270 --> 01:12:15.690
- Everyone. please come.
- Happy birthday!

1669
01:12:15.770 --> 01:12:16.650
Let's cut the cake.

1670
01:12:16.730 --> 01:12:17.690
- Yes.
- Let's do this.

1671
01:12:20.730 --> 01:12:23.690
Happy birthday to you.

1672
01:12:23.850 --> 01:12:27.140
Jenny. happy birthday to you.

1673
01:12:27.270 --> 01:12:30.230
May God bless you. Jenny.

1674
01:12:30.310 --> 01:12:33.060
May God bless you. Jenny.

1675
01:12:33.140 --> 01:12:34.390
Say...

1676
01:12:39.680 --> 01:12:42.220
Happy birthday to you.

1677
01:12:42.310 --> 01:12:45.190
Happy birthday to you.

1678
01:12:45.270 --> 01:12:51.400
Happy birthday dear Jenny.
happy birthday to you.

1679
01:12:51.520 --> 01:12:53.020
Whoa!

1680
01:12:53.560 --> 01:12:54.690
Wait a minute.

1681
01:12:55.060 --> 01:12:57.480
I can't eat your birthday cake
just like that...

1682
01:12:57.560 --> 01:12:59.110
without saying something nice
about my wife.

1683
01:12:59.520 --> 01:13:00.270
Oh!

1684
01:13:00.350 --> 01:13:02.100
I would like to say a few words
about Jenny.

1685
01:13:02.600 --> 01:13:04.300
Jenny. you might be the third one
in my life...

1686
01:13:05.430 --> 01:13:06.140
Huh?

1687
01:13:06.480 --> 01:13:10.730
I mean. after mom and dad...

1688
01:13:11.600 --> 01:13:15.220
but for me. you're the first one.

1689
01:13:15.600 --> 01:13:21.100
The first to go to church.
the first to pray for me.

1690
01:13:21.180 --> 01:13:24.300
Come on Michael.
every Christian girl does that.

1691
01:13:24.480 --> 01:13:25.150
Just eat the cake.

1692
01:13:25.230 --> 01:13:26.980
He'll eat the cake. but the Roza...

1693
01:13:27.480 --> 01:13:28.360
Roza?

1694
01:13:28.430 --> 01:13:30.970
Roja. It's my favorite movie.

1695
01:13:31.060 --> 01:13:34.520
I told him we'd watch it together
in the theatre on Jenny's birthday.

1696
01:13:34.600 --> 01:13:36.970
but then someone told me
the movie left theatres 30 years ago.

1697
01:13:37.060 --> 01:13:38.310
You can show it to her later.

1698
01:13:38.390 --> 01:13:39.470
You can show her later.

1699
01:13:39.770 --> 01:13:41.310
First. have the cake.

1700
01:13:41.390 --> 01:13:44.140
Cake... I'll eat it.
but before that. I'll make a vow.

1701
01:13:44.230 --> 01:13:46.020
Bro. you'll need more time...
one vow won't be enough.

1702
01:13:46.350 --> 01:13:49.430
Yeah. even an enemy can make one vow...

1703
01:13:49.600 --> 01:13:50.760
I'll make a couple of them.

1704
01:13:50.890 --> 01:13:55.180
Jenny. I vow that I'll care
for your happiness before mine.

1705
01:13:55.270 --> 01:13:56.150
How sweet...

1706
01:13:59.310 --> 01:13:59.980
And I vow...

1707
01:14:00.060 --> 01:14:01.110
It's 6:15 pm...

1708
01:14:01.270 --> 01:14:02.520
- It's 6:15 pm...?
- Hmm.

1709
01:14:02.600 --> 01:14:03.550
It's 6:15...

1710
01:14:03.640 --> 01:14:09.220
And I vow that I won't waste
any more time and eat the cake!

1711
01:14:09.310 --> 01:14:10.480
Happy birthday. darling.

1712
01:14:11.520 --> 01:14:12.940
Yay!

1713
01:14:13.270 --> 01:14:14.110
Happy birthday.

1714
01:14:14.180 --> 01:14:15.260
Thank you.

1715
01:14:16.730 --> 01:14:17.810
I too have got something for you.

1716
01:14:17.890 --> 01:14:18.640
- Hubby...
- Yes.

1717
01:14:21.600 --> 01:14:22.800
Happy birthday. darling.

1718
01:14:23.520 --> 01:14:24.520
Banana!

1719
01:14:24.600 --> 01:14:26.890
When God gives you a banana honey.
eat it as a holy offering. Jenny.

1720
01:14:27.020 --> 01:14:29.150
But first. touch it to your forehead.

1721
01:14:29.850 --> 01:14:32.470
Michael. did you put on a tika?
(vermillion/injection shot)? 

1722
01:14:32.560 --> 01:14:34.230
No. the last shot I took was for corona.

1723
01:14:34.310 --> 01:14:35.560
The rest. I got as a kid.

1724
01:14:35.640 --> 01:14:36.640
I'm not talking about that.

1725
01:14:37.310 --> 01:14:38.400
This red mark on your forehead...

1726
01:14:38.810 --> 01:14:39.810
My forehead?

1727
01:14:39.930 --> 01:14:40.850
Is it too red?

1728
01:14:40.930 --> 01:14:41.850
Yes.

1729
01:14:43.020 --> 01:14:47.650
Oh. it gets red like that...
allergy. I think.

1730
01:14:47.680 --> 01:14:49.180
Allergy to what?

1731
01:14:49.390 --> 01:14:50.390
- Well...
- To cake.

1732
01:14:50.480 --> 01:14:51.440
- Yeah.
- He just had some...

1733
01:14:51.520 --> 01:14:52.020
so it got triggered.

1734
01:14:52.100 --> 01:14:55.640
Actually. if it weren't Jenny's birthday.
I'd never eat it.

1735
01:14:55.890 --> 01:14:58.600
Baby... baby. that's so sweet of you.

1736
01:14:58.640 --> 01:14:59.640
It's okay. baby.

1737
01:15:00.640 --> 01:15:02.350
I too have planned a gift for you.

1738
01:15:02.430 --> 01:15:03.600
- Seriously?
- Come.

1739
01:15:05.890 --> 01:15:07.600
Wait... wait a second...

1740
01:15:09.430 --> 01:15:10.640
Only the forehead turns red?

1741
01:15:11.350 --> 01:15:13.140
No. a few other places too.

1742
01:15:13.230 --> 01:15:15.480
But I can't really show those
in front of the guests.

1743
01:15:15.560 --> 01:15:16.440
Hey!

1744
01:15:16.520 --> 01:15:17.520
Come.

1745
01:15:21.810 --> 01:15:24.520
Sir. his turns red. mine turns blue.

1746
01:15:24.600 --> 01:15:25.600
- Want to see?
- Shut up.

1747
01:15:26.680 --> 01:15:27.850
Go offer cake to everyone.

1748
01:15:43.680 --> 01:15:44.930
And this is what I brought for you.

1749
01:15:46.060 --> 01:15:46.900
This...?

1750
01:15:49.350 --> 01:15:51.300
Like you kept a fast for our marriage.

1751
01:15:51.810 --> 01:15:55.310
I did a Pooja (veneration) for my wife's
and my family's happiness.

1752
01:15:55.390 --> 01:15:56.260
Huh?

1753
01:15:56.680 --> 01:15:59.180
I worshipped. I prayed.

1754
01:15:59.680 --> 01:16:04.760
Our family will be complete only
when we have a child.

1755
01:16:04.980 --> 01:16:05.810
A child?

1756
01:16:06.430 --> 01:16:08.760
What's the rush?

1757
01:16:09.140 --> 01:16:13.390
When there's a kid. a man thinks
at least four times before divorcing.

1758
01:16:13.730 --> 01:16:17.480
I want you to think twenty times.

1759
01:16:17.560 --> 01:16:18.650
What do you mean?

1760
01:16:18.850 --> 01:16:20.550
I mean I want five kids.

1761
01:16:20.890 --> 01:16:22.430
Do you want to be a mother
or open a madrasa?

1762
01:16:22.600 --> 01:16:23.640
Open a madrasa!

1763
01:16:27.180 --> 01:16:30.010
Saniya.
what the hell did you trap me into?

1764
01:16:36.140 --> 01:16:37.550
Hey. make it a bit crisper.

1765
01:16:37.890 --> 01:16:39.140
Make it a bit crisper.

1766
01:16:39.230 --> 01:16:40.690
The pan's crisp too.
want me to bring that along?

1767
01:16:41.640 --> 01:16:43.550
Ruhi. I...

1768
01:16:45.310 --> 01:16:46.190
Biryani.

1769
01:16:46.270 --> 01:16:47.730
No. the one eating it!

1770
01:16:47.810 --> 01:16:48.730
Rizwan.

1771
01:16:48.810 --> 01:16:50.190
Son. this is your abbu.

1772
01:16:50.270 --> 01:16:51.270
Abbu?

1773
01:16:51.480 --> 01:16:53.770
Yeah. he's my aunt's son.

1774
01:16:53.980 --> 01:16:56.610
She passed away.
so he's going to be living with us now.

1775
01:16:56.770 --> 01:16:58.230
He's the one I mentioned last night.

1776
01:16:58.640 --> 01:17:00.550
You don't have any problem. right?

1777
01:17:00.810 --> 01:17:05.610
No. God sent me into this world.
Allah sent me to look after people.

1778
01:17:05.680 --> 01:17:07.010
So. I'll look after him as well.

1779
01:17:07.100 --> 01:17:08.140
Go on. eat. son.

1780
01:17:08.230 --> 01:17:09.810
Son. say hello to Abbu.

1781
01:17:10.140 --> 01:17:11.100
Hello. Abbu.

1782
01:17:11.180 --> 01:17:12.430
When are you going to get me sweets?

1783
01:17:12.520 --> 01:17:13.900
Sweets? For what?

1784
01:17:14.060 --> 01:17:16.360
You just became a father.
Sweets are a must!

1785
01:17:17.390 --> 01:17:18.220
Naughty.

1786
01:17:18.310 --> 01:17:19.190
You can surely have some sweets. son.

1787
01:17:19.270 --> 01:17:20.230
Eat this first.

1788
01:17:20.310 --> 01:17:20.860
I'll get going now.

1789
01:17:20.930 --> 01:17:21.850
Have some.

1790
01:17:21.930 --> 01:17:23.390
No Ammi. I'll eat at the restaurant.

1791
01:17:23.520 --> 01:17:24.480
Have some.

1792
01:17:25.230 --> 01:17:26.770
If he spares some. send it over.

1793
01:17:29.980 --> 01:17:31.480
Go on. eat. Here. have this.

1794
01:17:32.350 --> 01:17:33.140
Which one do you want?

1795
01:17:33.230 --> 01:17:34.360
- This one.
- Red?

1796
01:17:34.430 --> 01:17:35.850
- Yes. red.
- Say thank you.

1797
01:17:37.350 --> 01:17:38.100
Yes.

1798
01:17:38.180 --> 01:17:39.100
Good boy.

1799
01:17:39.270 --> 01:17:40.650
Did everyone get it?
Yes?

1800
01:17:41.560 --> 01:17:42.480
Meera?

1801
01:17:43.060 --> 01:17:44.440
Hey. you're home early.

1802
01:17:45.730 --> 01:17:46.940
How many aunts of yours died?

1803
01:17:47.020 --> 01:17:47.860
Aunts?

1804
01:17:48.020 --> 01:17:49.610
Those are your aunt's kids. right?

1805
01:17:49.640 --> 01:17:50.760
Why will they be my aunt's kids?

1806
01:17:50.850 --> 01:17:51.850
They're the neighborhood kids.

1807
01:17:52.060 --> 01:17:53.190
I started giving tuition.

1808
01:17:53.270 --> 01:17:54.270
I see.

1809
01:17:54.350 --> 01:17:54.970
Nice kids.

1810
01:17:55.060 --> 01:17:55.730
Hello. kids.

1811
01:17:55.810 --> 01:17:57.560
- Hi. Uncle.
- Kids. you can come back tomorrow.

1812
01:17:57.600 --> 01:17:59.010
- Bye.
- Don't forget to finish your homework.

1813
01:17:59.140 --> 01:17:59.930
Bye. kids.

1814
01:18:00.020 --> 01:18:01.060
- Bye.
- Bye.

1815
01:18:01.140 --> 01:18:01.970
Bye-bye.

1816
01:18:02.060 --> 01:18:02.860
Bye-bye.

1817
01:18:02.930 --> 01:18:04.970
- Bye. sir. ma'am.
- Bye. son.

1818
01:18:06.730 --> 01:18:07.650
He's so cute.

1819
01:18:08.230 --> 01:18:10.900
Don't you think.
we should have one of our own?

1820
01:18:11.270 --> 01:18:12.980
Pick one from these.
any decent one would do.

1821
01:18:13.520 --> 01:18:15.560
I'm talking about our own child.

1822
01:18:15.600 --> 01:18:17.050
- Our own child.
- Our own child.

1823
01:18:17.140 --> 01:18:18.850
No. I want our own child.

1824
01:18:18.930 --> 01:18:21.390
- Fine. let me see.
- No. I want our own child.

1825
01:18:22.140 --> 01:18:23.180
Father.

1826
01:18:25.730 --> 01:18:26.900
Look. Father's coughing again.

1827
01:18:26.980 --> 01:18:28.480
Why won't you get him some medicine for it?

1828
01:18:28.560 --> 01:18:30.900
- No need.
- Father.

1829
01:18:31.100 --> 01:18:31.890
Bless you.

1830
01:18:31.980 --> 01:18:33.190
Who says you don't need it?

1831
01:18:33.270 --> 01:18:35.650
They stop romancing
as soon as you start coughing.

1832
01:18:35.730 --> 01:18:37.900
If they don't romance.
how will we get grandkids?

1833
01:18:37.980 --> 01:18:39.110
I'll get some tea for him.

1834
01:18:39.180 --> 01:18:41.350
Add some black pepper in it...
to cure his cough.

1835
01:18:41.520 --> 01:18:42.310
Sure. Mother.

1836
01:18:42.390 --> 01:18:43.760
Ma'am.
I brought your laundered clothes back.

1837
01:18:43.850 --> 01:18:45.970
- All night you kept coughing on my face.
- Show them.

1838
01:18:46.060 --> 01:18:46.980
Here you go.

1839
01:18:47.140 --> 01:18:48.600
Please count them.

1840
01:18:49.560 --> 01:18:50.610
Wait. wait. wait...

1841
01:18:51.310 --> 01:18:52.270
Hey. this isn't ours.

1842
01:18:52.350 --> 01:18:54.260
It was in your clothes. ma'am.

1843
01:18:54.350 --> 01:18:55.510
But it's a Muslim cap.

1844
01:18:55.730 --> 01:18:57.360
No one here wears that.

1845
01:18:57.430 --> 01:18:58.760
It's yours.

1846
01:18:58.850 --> 01:19:00.180
You have lost your mind.

1847
01:19:00.310 --> 01:19:02.650
You mixed up our clothes
with someone else's clothes?

1848
01:19:02.680 --> 01:19:05.300
No. I wash this pant all the time.

1849
01:19:05.390 --> 01:19:06.220
It was in it.

1850
01:19:06.310 --> 01:19:07.110
That's Mohan's pant.

1851
01:19:07.180 --> 01:19:08.010
That's what I said.

1852
01:19:08.100 --> 01:19:09.640
This is brother Mohan's pant.

1853
01:19:09.730 --> 01:19:10.900
Mohan's pant?

1854
01:19:10.980 --> 01:19:11.810
My pant?

1855
01:19:11.890 --> 01:19:13.220
How is that possible?

1856
01:19:14.100 --> 01:19:15.390
Have you ever seen me wearing
a cap like that?

1857
01:19:15.480 --> 01:19:16.560
But it came from your pant.

1858
01:19:16.600 --> 01:19:18.260
Why're you trying to prove it?

1859
01:19:18.350 --> 01:19:20.300
We said it's not ours.
just take it and leave.

1860
01:19:20.390 --> 01:19:21.640
- Take this.
- Wait.

1861
01:19:22.060 --> 01:19:22.940
Go.

1862
01:19:23.480 --> 01:19:24.480
Give me that cap.

1863
01:19:28.430 --> 01:19:29.350
Here...

1864
01:19:30.600 --> 01:19:31.720
Wear it.

1865
01:19:32.020 --> 01:19:32.730
Me?

1866
01:19:32.810 --> 01:19:34.900
Yes. you... wear it.

1867
01:19:41.520 --> 01:19:43.190
Wow. it fits perfectly.

1868
01:19:44.810 --> 01:19:46.520
Mohan's mother. come here.

1869
01:19:54.100 --> 01:19:57.010
Now twist your face. like this.

1870
01:19:59.100 --> 01:20:01.100
Twist it like this!

1871
01:20:03.770 --> 01:20:06.230
Brother. do this.

1872
01:20:06.980 --> 01:20:08.020
Don't you have any shame?

1873
01:20:08.100 --> 01:20:09.140
How can you make a face
in front of elders?

1874
01:20:09.230 --> 01:20:11.230
- Sorry.
- You do it... like this.

1875
01:20:11.810 --> 01:20:13.610
Like this? Like this. Father?

1876
01:20:13.640 --> 01:20:15.220
See. even she's doing it.

1877
01:20:15.310 --> 01:20:16.150
Come on. now you do it.

1878
01:20:16.230 --> 01:20:18.150
Close one eye and do this.

1879
01:20:18.770 --> 01:20:21.360
Mom. look at them.
they're acting like kids.

1880
01:20:21.430 --> 01:20:24.350
Old guys act like this
when there's no kid at home.

1881
01:20:24.430 --> 01:20:24.930
What?

1882
01:20:25.020 --> 01:20:26.400
Yes. Why are you doing this?

1883
01:20:26.810 --> 01:20:29.190
You don't get what I'm trying to do.

1884
01:20:29.310 --> 01:20:30.610
Come on. do it. Make a face.

1885
01:20:30.850 --> 01:20:32.350
Close one of your eyes and do this.

1886
01:20:33.390 --> 01:20:34.970
Like this?

1887
01:20:35.810 --> 01:20:37.190
Like this.

1888
01:20:37.770 --> 01:20:38.770
Like this?

1889
01:20:39.310 --> 01:20:40.310
Like this.

1890
01:20:40.390 --> 01:20:41.600
I can't do it.

1891
01:20:41.640 --> 01:20:43.140
Take this. I have a lot of stuff to do.

1892
01:20:43.230 --> 01:20:45.020
- He keeps asking me to make a face!
- Hey!

1893
01:20:45.140 --> 01:20:46.100
Mohan!

1894
01:20:50.230 --> 01:20:50.730
Excuse me.

1895
01:20:50.810 --> 01:20:51.560
Good day. Soham.

1896
01:20:51.640 --> 01:20:52.510
Thank you. ma'am.

1897
01:20:52.730 --> 01:20:53.560
Thank you.

1898
01:20:57.180 --> 01:20:58.550
Excuse me. ma'am.

1899
01:20:59.520 --> 01:21:00.690
- You?
- You!

1900
01:21:01.640 --> 01:21:03.470
We're both Hubby's wives... remember?

1901
01:21:03.560 --> 01:21:04.980
Of course. how can I forget that?

1902
01:21:05.060 --> 01:21:07.980
- Everyone was so confused.
- Especially that taxi driver.

1903
01:21:08.060 --> 01:21:09.440
Oh. my God!

1904
01:21:09.930 --> 01:21:11.430
So. what brings you here?

1905
01:21:11.520 --> 01:21:13.810
I came here for my son's admission.

1906
01:21:13.890 --> 01:21:14.800
Your son?

1907
01:21:14.890 --> 01:21:17.260
I mean my aunt's son.

1908
01:21:17.350 --> 01:21:19.470
My aunt passed away
so he's living with us now.

1909
01:21:19.560 --> 01:21:20.520
Oh. so sorry.

1910
01:21:20.730 --> 01:21:22.690
He missed school because of it.

1911
01:21:22.890 --> 01:21:24.300
He might take some time to catch up.

1912
01:21:24.390 --> 01:21:26.010
Please do the best you can.

1913
01:21:27.180 --> 01:21:27.930
No problem.

1914
01:21:28.060 --> 01:21:30.770
If you want you can send him to my house
for tuition from today itself.

1915
01:21:31.560 --> 01:21:32.150
Right?

1916
01:21:32.230 --> 01:21:34.400
You come too along.
we'll have some tea and chitchat.

1917
01:21:34.480 --> 01:21:35.360
Okay. Done.

1918
01:21:35.430 --> 01:21:36.510
I'll send you my address.

1919
01:21:47.810 --> 01:21:48.730
Bye. baby.

1920
01:21:48.810 --> 01:21:49.610
Bye.

1921
01:21:49.640 --> 01:21:50.680
Bye. see you.

1922
01:21:51.640 --> 01:21:53.100
Glory to Lord Ganesha!

1923
01:21:53.270 --> 01:21:54.520
Michael...?

1924
01:21:55.980 --> 01:21:57.730
He's the guy in charge here?

1925
01:21:57.890 --> 01:21:59.720
I mean. of course I'm Christian...

1926
01:22:00.180 --> 01:22:01.140
Did I say anything?

1927
01:22:01.270 --> 01:22:03.650
No. but you're a cop's sister.
who knows what might make you suspicious.

1928
01:22:03.730 --> 01:22:05.060
You think I doubt you?

1929
01:22:05.140 --> 01:22:06.760
- No. I just...
- I was saying I'll be late.

1930
01:22:06.850 --> 01:22:08.100
so I'll see you in the evening. okay?

1931
01:22:08.180 --> 01:22:09.010
- Oh. okay. See you.
- Bye.

1932
01:22:12.810 --> 01:22:13.520
Yes. Meera?

1933
01:22:13.600 --> 01:22:14.970
You're picking me up from school. right?

1934
01:22:15.060 --> 01:22:15.730
Yes. I'm on my way.

1935
01:22:15.810 --> 01:22:17.310
- I've been waiting.
- I'm coming.

1936
01:22:29.480 --> 01:22:30.940
[Indistinct Chatter]

1937
01:22:31.730 --> 01:22:33.400
[Indistinct Chatter]

1938
01:22:35.640 --> 01:22:36.600
Mehmood?

1939
01:22:37.680 --> 01:22:38.600
What are you doing here?

1940
01:22:38.680 --> 01:22:40.180
What are you doing here?

1941
01:22:40.270 --> 01:22:42.020
I... I came here for Rizwan's admission.

1942
01:22:42.100 --> 01:22:42.890
You didn't enroll him. did you?

1943
01:22:42.980 --> 01:22:44.360
This school's reputation's bad.

1944
01:22:44.430 --> 01:22:46.180
The principal eloped
with a student's mother.

1945
01:22:46.270 --> 01:22:48.060
No. that's not true. It's a great school.

1946
01:22:48.140 --> 01:22:50.470
In fact. one of the teachers
is my friend. Meera.

1947
01:22:50.560 --> 01:22:51.230
Come. I'll introduce you.

1948
01:22:51.310 --> 01:22:52.360
I don't want to meet anyone.

1949
01:22:52.430 --> 01:22:53.050
- Let's go home.
- Let's go?

1950
01:22:53.140 --> 01:22:53.970
Rizwan must be hungry.

1951
01:22:54.060 --> 01:22:55.190
I'm not hungry.

1952
01:22:55.270 --> 01:22:56.610
You're not hungry today?

1953
01:22:59.980 --> 01:23:01.690
How'd you know I'd be here?

1954
01:23:01.810 --> 01:23:03.230
That's just how lucky I am...

1955
01:23:03.310 --> 01:23:05.560
I go looking for one.
end up finding another.

1956
01:23:05.640 --> 01:23:07.140
Not another. your wife.

1957
01:23:07.270 --> 01:23:08.360
Yeah. same thing.

1958
01:23:20.890 --> 01:23:22.640
Ammi. do I have to start attending
the tuition classes from today itself?

1959
01:23:22.730 --> 01:23:24.690
Yes. you have missed school
for six months.

1960
01:23:24.770 --> 01:23:25.730
You will have to attend them.

1961
01:23:26.060 --> 01:23:27.310
Go and pack your school bag.

1962
01:23:30.560 --> 01:23:31.940
Meera. sorry. I got late.

1963
01:23:32.020 --> 01:23:32.980
I'll be there in a bit.

1964
01:23:33.060 --> 01:23:34.690
I'm home.
You too come soon.

1965
01:23:34.980 --> 01:23:35.980
Father's gone...

1966
01:23:36.680 --> 01:23:38.010
What! Father!

1967
01:23:38.140 --> 01:23:39.470
I'm coming right away.

1968
01:23:41.390 --> 01:23:43.930
Hubby. come home right away.
Father's not well.

1969
01:23:44.020 --> 01:23:45.060
- What?
- Come home right away.

1970
01:23:45.140 --> 01:23:46.300
I'll talk to you once I get there.

1971
01:23:50.180 --> 01:23:51.180
Meera!

1972
01:23:51.810 --> 01:23:52.610
Meera!

1973
01:23:53.770 --> 01:23:54.810
Meera!

1974
01:24:09.600 --> 01:24:10.510
Meera?

1975
01:24:13.520 --> 01:24:14.770
You said Father's gone?

1976
