<i>Come on. let's have fun without a care.</i>

2007
01:27:28.680 --> 01:27:32.510
<i>Come on. let's have fun without a care.</i>

2008
01:27:32.600 --> 01:27:37.010
<i>Come on. let's have fun without a care.</i>

2009
01:27:41.180 --> 01:27:42.100
Abba!

2010
01:27:46.390 --> 01:27:47.300
Abba?

2011
01:27:47.730 --> 01:27:48.810
He's my husband.

2012
01:27:49.100 --> 01:27:50.140
Who's your Abba?

2013
01:27:54.270 --> 01:27:56.310
Oh with his back on me.
I thought he was my abba.

2014
01:27:56.480 --> 01:27:58.610
He has the same vest.

2015
01:27:59.680 --> 01:28:00.470
I see.

2016
01:28:00.560 --> 01:28:01.770
He might have the same vest.

2017
01:28:01.850 --> 01:28:03.100
- but he doesn't have the same face. right?
- Yeah.

2018
01:28:03.270 --> 01:28:03.900
Yeah.

2019
01:28:04.020 --> 01:28:04.730
Yeah.

2020
01:28:05.430 --> 01:28:06.300
What yeah?

2021
01:28:06.640 --> 01:28:08.010
No. the face's totally different.

2022
01:28:08.810 --> 01:28:10.400
See? The face's totally different.

2023
01:28:10.930 --> 01:28:13.140
In this world. there are seven people
who look exactly alike.

2024
01:28:13.600 --> 01:28:16.100
So if one day you see someone
with my face with another woman.

2025
01:28:16.230 --> 01:28:17.810
don't start doubting me.

2026
01:28:17.890 --> 01:28:18.680
I don't doubt you.

2027
01:28:18.770 --> 01:28:22.610
You never know with wives. no one can
tell what might trigger suspicion.

2028
01:28:23.020 --> 01:28:25.110
Son. will you come at this time every day?

2029
01:28:26.770 --> 01:28:28.690
- No. he just came early today.
- I see.

2030
01:28:28.770 --> 01:28:30.020
Then from tomorrow.
I'll call him a little later.

2031
01:28:30.100 --> 01:28:31.050
Go home. son.

2032
01:28:31.230 --> 01:28:32.400
Can I drop you home. Rizwan?

2033
01:28:32.730 --> 01:28:33.610
Wait...

2034
01:28:34.560 --> 01:28:35.650
How do you know his name?

2035
01:28:36.930 --> 01:28:38.010
His name...

2036
01:28:38.850 --> 01:28:40.100
it's on his bag.

2037
01:28:40.180 --> 01:28:40.970
Show it to her.

2038
01:28:41.560 --> 01:28:42.440
See?

2039
01:28:42.640 --> 01:28:45.220
No. but the bag is on his back.

2040
01:28:45.680 --> 01:28:47.050
When did you read his name?

2041
01:28:48.020 --> 01:28:49.060
When he came in...

2042
01:28:49.140 --> 01:28:49.680
Okay.

2043
01:28:49.770 --> 01:28:51.400
- He was holding his bag in the front.
- Okay.

2044
01:28:51.480 --> 01:28:52.150
Right?

2045
01:28:52.230 --> 01:28:53.900
Yes. I was. Uncle is right.

2046
01:28:54.060 --> 01:28:54.900
Yes.

2047
01:28:54.980 --> 01:28:55.770
Brother!

2048
01:28:55.930 --> 01:28:57.640
He could never get my name right.

2049
01:28:57.730 --> 01:28:59.020
He's gone before he ever could.

2050
01:28:59.100 --> 01:29:00.470
He's not gone.

2051
01:29:01.230 --> 01:29:02.480
Tell him where Father is.

2052
01:29:02.890 --> 01:29:03.890
Where is he?

2053
01:29:04.890 --> 01:29:05.640
Bye.

2054
01:29:08.850 --> 01:29:10.100
I nearly died.

2055
01:29:10.430 --> 01:29:11.600
- How?
- Look over here.

2056
01:29:16.100 --> 01:29:17.050
Rizwan. my child...

2057
01:29:17.140 --> 01:29:18.260
What is he doing here?

2058
01:29:18.640 --> 01:29:19.640
What is he doing here?

2059
01:29:21.140 --> 01:29:23.390
Why'd you drag me all the way out here?

2060
01:29:23.480 --> 01:29:25.690
Son. we just came to make you understand.

2061
01:29:25.930 --> 01:29:29.430
if you tell anyone
that this man's got three wives...

2062
01:29:29.520 --> 01:29:30.310
Three wives?

2063
01:29:30.390 --> 01:29:32.100
Two! Two! What are you saying?

2064
01:29:32.180 --> 01:29:33.180
Yeah. two.

2065
01:29:33.520 --> 01:29:35.360
If you tell anyone.

2066
01:29:35.520 --> 01:29:38.610
I'll strip you naked
and throw you in the lake.

2067
01:29:38.640 --> 01:29:39.390
Wait...

2068
01:29:39.980 --> 01:29:41.610
The state I caught him.

2069
01:29:42.180 --> 01:29:44.180
shouldn't I be the one
getting threatened him?

2070
01:29:44.310 --> 01:29:45.270
You are right. son.

2071
01:29:45.350 --> 01:29:46.760
That was his idea.

2072
01:29:46.850 --> 01:29:48.300
I brought you here just
for a boat ride. really.

2073
01:29:48.600 --> 01:29:50.100
I love you. kid.

2074
01:29:50.270 --> 01:29:52.440
You want your abbu dead?

2075
01:29:52.680 --> 01:29:53.220
Right.

2076
01:29:53.310 --> 01:29:56.770
If you tell Ruhi or Meera about this.
I'll jump straight into this lake.

2077
01:29:56.850 --> 01:29:57.720
Wait...

2078
01:29:58.140 --> 01:30:00.260
If you jump. who'll buy me a PS5?

2079
01:30:01.180 --> 01:30:02.010
PS5?

2080
01:30:02.100 --> 01:30:04.010
We grew up playing marbles. son.

2081
01:30:04.100 --> 01:30:05.180
How about a bicycle instead?

2082
01:30:05.270 --> 01:30:06.150
- Yes. a bicycle?
- A bicycle?

2083
01:30:06.230 --> 01:30:07.650
- Yeah.
- I'm not a kid.

2084
01:30:07.730 --> 01:30:09.230
Then take a truck. run it over me

2085
01:30:09.310 --> 01:30:10.610
- and crush your father.
- Go.

2086
01:30:11.180 --> 01:30:12.220
Listen son.

2087
01:30:12.600 --> 01:30:15.180
Hubby. get him whatever he wants.

2088
01:30:15.560 --> 01:30:16.310
Okay?

2089
01:30:16.520 --> 01:30:17.440
Done. son.

2090
01:30:17.520 --> 01:30:18.980
Don't tell anyone. okay?

2091
01:30:19.060 --> 01:30:19.980
- I won't.
- Promise.

2092
01:30:20.310 --> 01:30:20.860
Okay.

2093
01:30:20.930 --> 01:30:21.850
Good boy.

2094
01:30:21.930 --> 01:30:22.430
Love you.

2095
01:30:22.520 --> 01:30:23.770
- He's such a good boy.
- Let's go home now.

2096
01:30:23.850 --> 01:30:25.050
A very good boy.

2097
01:30:25.140 --> 01:30:27.600
He wants a PS5. huh?

2098
01:30:28.310 --> 01:30:30.020
What games are you planning to play?

2099
01:30:30.140 --> 01:30:30.760
FIFA.

2100
01:30:30.850 --> 01:30:32.720
The same games you're already playing
with your father?

2101
01:30:32.850 --> 01:30:34.550
I've got you everything you asked for.

2102
01:30:34.600 --> 01:30:35.510
Are you happy now?

2103
01:30:35.600 --> 01:30:36.050
Yeah.

2104
01:30:36.140 --> 01:30:38.390
Now you won't tell anyone
how many wives your father has. right?

2105
01:30:39.020 --> 01:30:40.190
No. I won't.

2106
01:30:40.270 --> 01:30:42.190
- Very good.
- Oh no.

2107
01:30:42.270 --> 01:30:44.690
Madam. three wives and now a kid.

2108
01:30:44.770 --> 01:30:46.060
Impossible!

2109
01:30:46.140 --> 01:30:47.600
I should call Surleen right away.

2110
01:30:49.060 --> 01:30:50.150
Hello. Surleen?

2111
01:30:50.430 --> 01:30:51.260
Yes.

2112
01:30:51.390 --> 01:30:52.470
You didn't get engaged to the guy. did you?

2113
01:30:52.560 --> 01:30:53.940
- Why?
- Call it off.

2114
01:30:54.480 --> 01:30:59.860
Your man's got three accounts
and one small FD too.

2115
01:31:00.270 --> 01:31:02.150
- I mean he's also got a child.
- Yes.

2116
01:31:02.310 --> 01:31:03.150
He has a child.

2117
01:31:03.230 --> 01:31:03.980
Do you have any proof?

2118
01:31:04.060 --> 01:31:05.360
What? Proof?

2119
01:31:05.810 --> 01:31:07.060
I will send you the proof.

2120
01:31:07.180 --> 01:31:08.800
I'll send it on time.
Okay?

2121
01:31:08.890 --> 01:31:11.550
Then everything'll be milk and milk.
and water and water.

2122
01:31:11.600 --> 01:31:13.470
She means everything
will be crystal clear.

2123
01:31:13.560 --> 01:31:15.020
- Same thing.
- Listen...

2124
01:31:18.770 --> 01:31:19.690
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

2125
01:31:21.600 --> 01:31:22.430
Good morning. ma'am.

2126
01:31:22.520 --> 01:31:23.730
Good morning. kids.

2127
01:31:27.100 --> 01:31:27.970
Meera...

2128
01:31:28.770 --> 01:31:30.560
- your purse. You always forget.
- So sorry.

2129
01:31:30.640 --> 01:31:31.600
Okay. bye.

2130
01:31:31.640 --> 01:31:32.890
- Good morning. ma'am.
- Good morning.

2131
01:31:33.230 --> 01:31:34.110
Hello.

2132
01:31:34.180 --> 01:31:35.600
Actually. my husband Mohan.

2133
01:31:35.640 --> 01:31:36.350
Hello.

2134
01:31:36.430 --> 01:31:37.600
Good you came here.

2135
01:31:37.680 --> 01:31:39.260
We're holding a blood donation camp today.

2136
01:31:39.350 --> 01:31:40.010
Oh nice.

2137
01:31:40.100 --> 01:31:42.430
You must help us in this noble cause.

2138
01:31:42.890 --> 01:31:44.640
Meera. I'll catch you later.

2139
01:31:44.680 --> 01:31:45.550
Sure.

2140
01:31:45.600 --> 01:31:46.300
I'll get going as well.

2141
01:31:46.430 --> 01:31:47.050
No! Where are you going?

2142
01:31:47.140 --> 01:31:48.760
Didn't you hear her? It's a noble cause.

2143
01:31:48.850 --> 01:31:49.550
Come on. donate your blood.

2144
01:31:49.600 --> 01:31:51.470
Ever since I got married.
I've stopped producing blood.

2145
01:31:51.810 --> 01:31:52.980
I haven't drained you that much.

2146
01:31:53.060 --> 01:31:53.940
Let's go.

2147
01:31:58.730 --> 01:31:59.560
What is his name?

2148
01:31:59.600 --> 01:32:01.640
Mohan Sharma.

2149
01:32:01.730 --> 01:32:02.440
My husband.

2150
01:32:02.520 --> 01:32:04.480
Mohan Sharma.
What's his age?

2151
01:32:04.730 --> 01:32:05.810
- 32.
- 32.

2152
01:32:05.930 --> 01:32:08.180
Ma'am. principal maam's calling you.

2153
01:32:08.350 --> 01:32:09.050
I'm coming.

2154
01:32:09.140 --> 01:32:11.720
"You give me blood. I give you freedom."

2155
01:32:11.810 --> 01:32:12.610
What will you say?

2156
01:32:12.680 --> 01:32:15.010
"You give me biryani. I'm feeling hungry."

2157
01:32:15.140 --> 01:32:17.260
Oh God. where's the tiffin?

2158
01:32:17.430 --> 01:32:19.050
Near the coffee counter.

2159
01:32:19.310 --> 01:32:20.860
Come on. give me an energy drink.

2160
01:32:21.600 --> 01:32:22.760
- Here you go. sir.
- Thank you.

2161
01:32:25.430 --> 01:32:26.600
Mehmood?

2162
01:32:27.350 --> 01:32:28.510
What am I doing here?

2163
01:32:28.600 --> 01:32:29.600
What are you doing here?

2164
01:32:29.640 --> 01:32:30.720
What are you doing here?

2165
01:32:31.560 --> 01:32:32.730
I came to take you home.

2166
01:32:32.810 --> 01:32:34.230
They're taking people's blood here.

2167
01:32:34.310 --> 01:32:35.440
- Let's go home.
- They aren't taking anyone's blood forcibly.

2168
01:32:35.520 --> 01:32:36.360
It's a blood donation camp.

2169
01:32:36.430 --> 01:32:37.180
You have to donate blood. Let's go.

2170
01:32:37.270 --> 01:32:38.060
I already did.

2171
01:32:38.140 --> 01:32:39.220
There's no way you already did.
Let's go.

2172
01:32:39.310 --> 01:32:40.360
You can ask them.

2173
01:32:42.560 --> 01:32:44.110
- He will feel a little weak.
- Sir. sir...

2174
01:32:44.180 --> 01:32:45.510
- Did he donate?
- Who?

2175
01:32:47.600 --> 01:32:48.850
He's always so scared.

2176
01:32:48.980 --> 01:32:50.060
Did he donate?

2177
01:32:50.640 --> 01:32:51.640
He is...?

2178
01:32:52.560 --> 01:32:53.980
Mehmood. my husband.

2179
01:32:59.350 --> 01:33:02.470
Mohan's has... but Mehmood hasn't.

2180
01:33:02.560 --> 01:33:03.360
I knew it.

2181
01:33:03.430 --> 01:33:04.930
Come on. go and donate blood.

2182
01:33:07.980 --> 01:33:09.400
- B block.
- Okay.

2183
01:33:10.350 --> 01:33:11.600
- How old is he?
- 32.

2184
01:33:14.390 --> 01:33:15.300
Same.

2185
01:33:16.850 --> 01:33:17.720
Go on.

2186
01:33:18.310 --> 01:33:19.310
Keep going straight.

2187
01:33:19.770 --> 01:33:21.650
Mr. Gupta. this is the final list.

2188
01:33:22.100 --> 01:33:22.970
Meera!

2189
01:33:23.140 --> 01:33:23.850
Ruhi!

2190
01:33:23.980 --> 01:33:25.310
- Hi!
- You donated your blood?

2191
01:33:25.390 --> 01:33:27.470
Not yet. my husband's donating right now.

2192
01:33:27.560 --> 01:33:29.480
My husband too donated it.

2193
01:33:29.560 --> 01:33:30.610
He must be around.

2194
01:33:30.680 --> 01:33:31.350
I can't see him.

2195
01:33:31.430 --> 01:33:32.800
- He's here?
- Yes.

2196
01:33:32.890 --> 01:33:33.890
Let's make them meet each other then.

2197
01:33:33.980 --> 01:33:35.230
- Finally.
- Come.

2198
01:33:35.310 --> 01:33:38.650
Meera. meet Jenny
from Criticare Asia Hospital.

2199
01:33:38.810 --> 01:33:39.440
- Hi.
- Hi!

2200
01:33:39.520 --> 01:33:41.480
She's the one who organized this camp.

2201
01:33:42.020 --> 01:33:43.400
- Hello.
- Hello.

2202
01:33:43.480 --> 01:33:44.610
How lovely.

2203
01:33:44.640 --> 01:33:46.510
Your hospital does a lot of charity.

2204
01:33:46.600 --> 01:33:48.850
and now this camp gave us a chance
to help too.

2205
01:33:48.930 --> 01:33:49.970
Thank you so much. Jenny.

2206
01:33:50.060 --> 01:33:51.980
I should be the one thanking you guys.

2207
01:33:52.140 --> 01:33:53.930
The response
from your school's been great.

2208
01:33:54.020 --> 01:33:55.860
And the teachers are really cooperative.

2209
01:33:58.180 --> 01:33:59.600
Where's Dr. Anjali?

2210
01:34:00.180 --> 01:34:01.010
A block.

2211
01:34:01.310 --> 01:34:02.270
- I'll see you.
- See you.

2212
01:34:02.350 --> 01:34:03.390
Bye.

2213
01:34:04.810 --> 01:34:05.980
Don't you guys have straws?

2214
01:34:11.680 --> 01:34:12.600
Michael?

2215
01:34:12.680 --> 01:34:13.600
You...?

2216
01:34:14.020 --> 01:34:15.230
You too are here?

2217
01:34:15.430 --> 01:34:17.010
Yeah. I organized this camp.

2218
01:34:17.100 --> 01:34:18.640
I already gave my blood twice.

2219
01:34:18.680 --> 01:34:19.550
I'm not giving it again.

2220
01:34:19.640 --> 01:34:20.600
Twice? When?

2221
01:34:21.730 --> 01:34:24.650
Once when I was 18.
and once when I was 24.

2222
01:34:24.980 --> 01:34:26.520
You can donate every three months.
Let's go.

2223
01:34:26.600 --> 01:34:29.300
Every three months.
not every three minutes!

2224
01:34:29.430 --> 01:34:30.510
I've already donated my blood.

2225
01:34:30.600 --> 01:34:31.470
Has he donated?

2226
01:34:32.520 --> 01:34:33.480
He is...?

2227
01:34:33.560 --> 01:34:34.860
Michael. my husband.

2228
01:34:35.060 --> 01:34:38.150
Oh... Michael.

2229
01:34:38.350 --> 01:34:39.600
Mohan and Mehmood are done. but...

2230
01:34:39.640 --> 01:34:40.930
Michael hasn't. right?

2231
01:34:41.430 --> 01:34:42.010
Fine. I'll donate!

2232
01:34:42.100 --> 01:34:44.100
If Mohan and Mehmood can donate
then why not Michael as well?

2233
01:34:44.180 --> 01:34:44.850
Where do I go?

2234
01:34:45.270 --> 01:34:45.900
C block.

2235
01:34:45.980 --> 01:34:47.810
Fine. I'll see your later!

2236
01:34:48.140 --> 01:34:49.180
Age 32. right?

2237
01:34:49.560 --> 01:34:50.520
Good guess.

2238
01:34:50.600 --> 01:34:51.600
Yes.

2239
01:34:55.850 --> 01:34:59.430
"You give me blood. I give you freedom!"

2240
01:35:02.770 --> 01:35:06.110
"See no evil. speak no evil.
hear no evil."

2241
01:35:06.520 --> 01:35:09.150
"No religion is greater
than non-violence."

2242
01:35:11.270 --> 01:35:13.610
'Kids. you are the future of my country."

2243
01:35:13.640 --> 01:35:15.890
"You will build my dream India."

2244
01:35:25.930 --> 01:35:28.970
Mohan. Mehmood. and Michael...

2245
01:35:30.020 --> 01:35:34.730
If it were just about donating blood.
I'd praise you.

2246
01:35:35.350 --> 01:35:36.890
But cheating three women?

2247
01:35:39.230 --> 01:35:40.520
It's not so. brother.

2248
01:35:40.930 --> 01:35:43.260
They formed a kitty party...
I just came out the winner.

2249
01:35:43.730 --> 01:35:44.810
They're all happy.

2250
01:35:44.890 --> 01:35:46.680
Fine. I'll ask them myself.

2251
01:35:46.890 --> 01:35:49.470
- Wait... what do you want?
- "Long live revolution!"

2252
01:35:51.180 --> 01:35:52.350
Rs. 50.000.

2253
01:35:52.680 --> 01:35:54.220
How about if I pay Rs.500 a month?

2254
01:35:54.430 --> 01:35:56.050
You think I'm a beggar or what?

2255
01:35:56.520 --> 01:35:58.650
I'm thinking Rs. 50.000 every month.

2256
01:35:59.640 --> 01:36:01.680
And I'm thinking of strangling you.

2257
01:36:01.810 --> 01:36:03.560
once I can get my hands on your neck.

2258
01:36:04.930 --> 01:36:09.350
Fine. we'll see whose neck
gets grabbed soon enough.

2259
01:36:09.930 --> 01:36:11.390
I'll expose you in public.

2260
01:36:11.480 --> 01:36:14.190
A huge round of applause for all the kids.

2261
01:36:17.930 --> 01:36:19.180
Excuse me. ma'am.

2262
01:36:20.850 --> 01:36:23.800
Don't go anywhere.
the climax's still to come.

2263
01:36:24.310 --> 01:36:28.400
And now. let's meet a man...

2264
01:36:28.890 --> 01:36:33.600
who's married three times.
in three different faiths...

2265
01:36:35.270 --> 01:36:39.190
and whose three wives
have no clue about it.

2266
01:36:40.310 --> 01:36:41.900
But today. they'll know the truth.

2267
01:36:42.680 --> 01:36:45.260
That man is right here among us.

2268
01:36:46.560 --> 01:36:47.650
Why are you standing there?

2269
01:36:47.730 --> 01:36:48.730
Come up. everyone would love to meet you.

2270
01:36:48.810 --> 01:36:50.060
Come on the stage.

2271
01:36:50.140 --> 01:36:51.140
Please. join us.

2272
01:36:53.180 --> 01:36:54.180
Come on.

2273
01:37:02.390 --> 01:37:03.430
Mohan?

2274
01:37:05.350 --> 01:37:06.390
Mehmood?

2275
01:37:06.850 --> 01:37:07.800
Michael?

2276
01:37:09.810 --> 01:37:12.310
Why do you all look so surprised?

2277
01:37:14.060 --> 01:37:15.520
You all know me.

2278
01:37:16.890 --> 01:37:18.140
I'm your Mohan.

2279
01:37:19.890 --> 01:37:21.050
your Mehmood.

2280
01:37:22.600 --> 01:37:23.680
and your Michael too.

2281
01:37:25.810 --> 01:37:28.400
I'm Jain. I'm Sikh.

2282
01:37:28.850 --> 01:37:31.390
I'm North. I'm South.

2283
01:37:32.350 --> 01:37:34.640
I'm East and I'm West.

2284
01:37:35.390 --> 01:37:37.930
Punjab. Sindh. Gujarat. Maratha.

2285
01:37:38.270 --> 01:37:39.690
I'm your Hindustan!

2286
01:37:50.020 --> 01:37:53.060
Someone said I have three homes...

2287
01:37:53.560 --> 01:37:57.520
No. I embraced all cultures.

2288
01:37:58.480 --> 01:38:02.650
Sikh. Jain. Parsi... they're all mine.

2289
01:38:03.480 --> 01:38:04.650
I don't belong to one.

2290
01:38:04.810 --> 01:38:07.810
I belong to everyone
and everyone belongs to me.

2291
01:38:08.810 --> 01:38:11.190
With one I pray.

2292
01:38:12.480 --> 01:38:14.310
with another I bow in worship.

2293
01:38:15.020 --> 01:38:18.190
and with another I touch
my heart and say. God bless.

2294
01:38:19.100 --> 01:38:22.180
I'm Christmas. I'm Diwali

2295
01:38:22.640 --> 01:38:25.010
I'm Eid. I'm Baisakhi...

2296
01:38:25.680 --> 01:38:28.640
I belong to all faiths.
and all of you belong to me.

2297
01:38:28.730 --> 01:38:30.650
Because I'm your Hindustan.

2298
01:38:31.600 --> 01:38:32.760
Jai Hind!

2299
01:38:33.350 --> 01:38:34.800
He's my husband.

2300
01:38:36.230 --> 01:38:38.150
I'm so proud of you. Michael.

2301
01:38:38.230 --> 01:38:39.480
Michael?

2302
01:38:39.890 --> 01:38:41.430
That's my husband.

2303
01:38:41.810 --> 01:38:43.020
PS5!

2304
01:38:43.100 --> 01:38:43.850
What?

2305
01:38:43.930 --> 01:38:45.640
My PS5's here!

2306
01:38:45.770 --> 01:38:47.020
Great. Mr. Gupta.

2307
01:38:47.390 --> 01:38:50.850
We couldn't have asked for a better finale
to the fancy dress competition than this.

2308
01:38:51.270 --> 01:38:52.190
Well...

2309
01:38:55.480 --> 01:38:56.900
Ladies and gentlemen.

2310
01:38:57.140 --> 01:38:59.970
please welcome our chief guest
for the evening...

2311
01:39:00.390 --> 01:39:03.850
Mr. Sukhvinder Singh Gill
and his daughter. Simran.

2312
01:39:37.480 --> 01:39:38.860
Saniya?!

2313
01:39:43.180 --> 01:39:44.600
Saniya!

2314
01:39:45.930 --> 01:39:47.140
Saniya!

2315
01:39:47.520 --> 01:39:48.690
Saniya!

2316
01:39:48.890 --> 01:39:50.800
- Stay back. Stay back.
- Saniya!

2317
01:39:50.980 --> 01:39:53.060
Saniya! Wait. sir. Saniya!

2318
01:39:53.140 --> 01:39:53.850
Where do you think you are going?

2319
01:39:53.930 --> 01:39:55.220
- Stay back.
- Can't you hear me?

2320
01:39:55.310 --> 01:39:56.190
Move back.

2321
01:39:57.180 --> 01:39:58.720
Ishaan as Bhagat Singh.

2322
01:40:00.140 --> 01:40:02.680
- Ridhaan as Nehru-ji.
- Hubby. something unbelievable just happened.

2323
01:40:02.980 --> 01:40:04.060
You won't believe this...

2324
01:40:04.140 --> 01:40:06.010
- Janvi as Rani Laxmibai.
- I found Saniya.

2325
01:40:06.100 --> 01:40:06.930
What?

2326
01:40:07.020 --> 01:40:08.110
She's right here in front of me.

2327
01:40:08.180 --> 01:40:09.680
- Rahul as Rabindranath Tagore.
- at Meera's school.

2328
01:40:09.770 --> 01:40:10.690
Get here. fast.

2329
01:40:11.310 --> 01:40:12.110
Yes.

2330
01:40:27.890 --> 01:40:30.140
Hey. who are you guys?

2331
01:40:30.560 --> 01:40:32.940
I noticed you following our cars.

2332
01:40:33.020 --> 01:40:33.860
What do you want?

2333
01:40:33.930 --> 01:40:35.890
Sir. that girl with Mr. Gill is my Saniya.

2334
01:40:35.980 --> 01:40:37.110
Who's Saniya?

2335
01:40:37.430 --> 01:40:39.470
She's Mr. Gill's daughter. Simran.

2336
01:40:39.560 --> 01:40:40.980
No. sir. she's Saniya.

2337
01:40:41.060 --> 01:40:41.940
I love her.

2338
01:40:42.020 --> 01:40:43.560
Have you lost your mind?

2339
01:40:43.640 --> 01:40:45.510
He's telling the truth. sir.
She's Saniya.

2340
01:40:45.600 --> 01:40:46.800
Shut up and get out of here.

2341
01:40:46.930 --> 01:40:48.430
I'm not leaving without meeting her.

2342
01:40:48.520 --> 01:40:50.360
So. you're not going to leave. huh?

2343
01:40:50.850 --> 01:40:51.760
Huh?

2344
01:40:51.850 --> 01:40:53.180
Cut my head off if you want.

2345
01:40:53.680 --> 01:40:56.890
but she's my Saniya
and I'm not leaving without meeting her.

2346
01:41:13.430 --> 01:41:14.890
You might be right. son.

2347
01:41:16.520 --> 01:41:18.310
She isn't Simran and she's your Saniya.

2348
01:41:19.600 --> 01:41:22.140
But she's forgotten everything.

2349
01:41:22.480 --> 01:41:23.360
How?

2350
01:41:23.430 --> 01:41:25.300
God knows if it was an accident...

2351
01:41:26.480 --> 01:41:28.110
or something worse.

2352
01:41:28.890 --> 01:41:33.050
She was unconscious
when Mr. Gill found her.

2353
01:41:33.520 --> 01:41:37.190
She got treated. but she lost her memory.

2354
01:41:38.060 --> 01:41:43.110
She didn't remember anything...
neither her name nor old her life.

2355
01:41:43.680 --> 01:41:46.850
Mr. Gill gave her a new one. Simran.

2356
01:41:47.480 --> 01:41:49.060
Now she's his daughter.

2357
01:41:49.730 --> 01:41:55.060
and he's going to marrying her
into a reputed Sikh family.

2358
01:41:57.520 --> 01:42:01.270
No problem. sir. Sardar Manjeet Singh
is ready to marry Simran.

2359
01:42:02.060 --> 01:42:03.230
Who's he?

2360
01:42:03.680 --> 01:42:04.720
Your brother.

2361
01:42:05.640 --> 01:42:06.890
So now you're going to be a Sikh?

2362
01:42:07.430 --> 01:42:10.300
Love isn't about changing;
it's about accepting. Hubby.

2363
01:42:10.640 --> 01:42:12.050
Well said. son.

2364
01:42:12.640 --> 01:42:16.220
We don't choose who we worship...

2365
01:42:17.230 --> 01:42:22.110
He chooses how
He wants to be worshipped through us.

2366
01:42:22.270 --> 01:42:23.230
Well said. sir.

2367
01:42:23.730 --> 01:42:25.810
Please bless him. sir.

2368
01:42:26.140 --> 01:42:27.550
May God bless you.

2369
01:42:28.020 --> 01:42:29.270
Thank you. sir.

2370
01:42:50.600 --> 01:42:54.050
<i>Ranjha found Heer. his soul's delight.</i>

2371
01:42:55.600 --> 01:42:59.100
<i>He found his destiny. his guiding light.</i>

2372
01:43:00.930 --> 01:43:05.640
<i>The thirsty found a river deep.</i>

2373
01:43:06.020 --> 01:43:09.270
<i>The weary at last found relief.</i>

2374
01:43:10.350 --> 01:43:15.260
<i>They crossed through fire holding strong.</i>

2375
01:43:15.560 --> 01:43:20.480
<i>They waited through the nights so long.</i>

2376
01:43:20.640 --> 01:43:22.930
<i>They spoke to each other
in dreams so deep.</i>

2377
01:43:23.020 --> 01:43:25.650
<i>That's how they loved
through nights of sleep.</i>

2378
01:43:25.730 --> 01:43:28.190
<i>Today they meet.</i>

2379
01:43:28.270 --> 01:43:31.400
<i>Their tears fulfil a lifelong dream.</i>

